    {
      "id": "458f04fb_74e7bf22",
      "file_path": "models-provider/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/provider/PolicyModelsProviderFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 38,
      "message": "These are the observed errors connecting to a docker db on a separate IP (VM). These are at about 1s resolution - i.e. it went from 'Connection refused' to 'Success' in a second with no intermediate (e.g. DB not ready) state\n\nNo /etc/hosts entry for mariadb\nInternal Exception: java.sql.SQLNonTransientConnectionException: Could not connect to address=(host=mariadb)(port=3306)(type=master) : mariadb\n... delay while I add entry\n/etc/hosts entry but VM not running\nInternal Exception: java.sql.SQLNonTransientConnectionException: Could not connect to address=(host=mariadb)(port=3306)(type=master) : No route to host (Host unreachable)\n... delay while I start VM\nVM running but DB not running\nInternal Exception: java.sql.SQLNonTransientConnectionException: Could not connect to address=(host=mariadb)(port=3306)(type=master) : Connection refused (Connection refused)\n... delay while I start DB\n... Success!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7010,
        "name": "Gregory Hayes",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "gregory.hayes@est.tech",
        "username": "gregory.hayes"
      },
      "updated": "2020-12-01 13:36:32.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "72a81e4b_285d8ff3",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a8d319a3_e76d5771",
      "file_path": "models-provider/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/provider/PolicyModelsProviderFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 38,
      "message": "I wonder if we could take an opposite approach and look for some things we know to be configuration errors, such as credential issues?  I've posted a query about this on onap-discuss, but haven't seen any replies yet.\n\nAnother approach to examining the error message content would be to always retry, but to limit the number of retries before giving up.  Nevertheless, I wouldn't make any more changes until I can get some more clarification and/or direction.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
